            "name": "קשת Keshet: For LGBTQ Equality in Jewish Life",
            "bio": "Founded by Jonathan Krasner and Jared Goldfarb in 1996, <span class=\"hebrew\">קשת</span> Keshet is a national organization in the United States working for the full equality of all LGBTQ Jews and their families in Jewish life. Besides strengthening Jewish communities, they equip Jewish organizations with the skills and knowledge to build LGBTQ-affirming communities; create spaces in which all queer Jewish youth feel seen and valued; and advance LGBTQ rights nationwide. Keshet has offices in the Bay Area, Chicago, and New York, in addition to their headquarters in Boston.",
